ingattempts to settle the palimony lawsuit against Navratilova. Gary DeShazo saidJerry Loftin, Nelson's lawyer, is seeking 40 percent of any settlement. &quot;Wewant (Loftin) to kick in money. That's the sticking point,&quot; DeShazo said.Loftin has been accused of improper conduct in the case. . . . The U.S.Olympic Committee appointed a special counsel to review the business recordsof USOC President Robert H. Helmick.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Staff and Wire Reports  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910912  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  September  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2G  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  373  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday, September 12, 199100256255,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>